              <p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="center"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">RESEARCH
              BASICS</font></b><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="center">&nbsp;
        </center>
            <p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Once
            a pure casting class reaches level 16, the researching skill will be
            an important one to master.&nbsp; A few spells, including some of
            the most powerful on that class arsenal, can only be obtained by
            researching.&nbsp; Even though you do not need to master the skill
            yourself (you can always ask a friend to research a spell for you),
            it is recommended that you do take Research as one of your
            skills.&nbsp; That way you don't have to rely on someone to succeed
            in researching that much needed spell.&nbsp; And you can always make
            some money from research.&nbsp; Simply research and sell spells you
            do not need.</font><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="left">&nbsp;<p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">In
            order to start researching, you must be at least <b>level 16</b>,
            own the <b>components</b> required for the spell you want to obtain
            and the corresponding <b>Research Book</b> of your class.&nbsp;
            Below is a list of component types and books that each class needs
            to research a spell.</font><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="left">&nbsp;<p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="left">&nbsp;
